  "r1": {
    "centrality": "methods/centrality.cljc — exact Brandes betweenness + power-iteration eigenvector + ΔΦ percolation/fragmentation sensitivity; L1 = C·(V/D)·(1+B'·)·(1−open) with real betweenness replacing the R0 bridge proxy",
    "join": "methods/join.cljc — live mirror JOIN: parse a sibling mirror's committed [e a v tx op] Datom log → lift into a domain layer → reconcile-by-label across layers. PROVEN on chie 智慧's real output (39 nodes/39 縁 → :ai layer). Running a mirror = G7-gated; joining a committed output = what kaname does.",
    "multiMirrorJoin": "founder-approved 2026-06-17 — per-mirror adapter registry (mirror-adapters) + join-mirrors joined 6 REAL committed mirror outputs (chie :ai · tsumugi :organization · inochi :ecology · hokorobi :economy · shiori :wellbecoming · web :economy) → ONE reconciled multilayer graph (173 nodes / 216 縁 / 5 domains; forms/datom auto-detect; per-mirror load-normalized). reconcile-by-label surfaced OpenAI/NVIDIA/Microsoft/TSMC/SoftBank/Anthropic as cross-domain entities; whole-multiplex 要 = OpenAI (V=3, L1 3.513); top bridges TSMC(betw 503)/NVIDIA(448). out/joined-sos-leverage.md. Re-running a mirror stays G7.",
    "webIngest": "methods/ingest.cljc (founder-approved 2026-06-17) — web→mirror pipeline: fetch a PUBLIC page (homepage / 公開投稿 / announcement) via babashka.http-client (fetch-text, anonymous GET, no-server-key) → extract DISCLOSED org relations via Murakumo local Ollama gemma-4-E4B-it-qat (ADR-2605215000) → mirror forms, every edge :en/basis = source URL + stated phrase (G5), person-excluded (G1), DISCLOSED-only (G4), representative lock-in load by kind (flagged). ingest-live! over data/ingest-sources.edn is the actor-runtime live leg (the actor fetches, not an operator tool). Ran on anthropic.com/news + nvidianews.nvidia.com → 10 orgs / 11 basis'd edges → data/ingested-web.kotoba.edn (:economy, :authoritative). Re-running live fetch+extraction is the G7 step; the committed .kotoba.edn is the durable artifact.",
    "langgraphActor": "kaname.graph (founder-approved 2026-06-17) — the actor's basic element is a langgraph-clj StateGraph (loads under babashka): :perceive-world(世界認識) → :leverage → :route → :osekkai → :persist. :perceive-world builds the cross-domain WORLD MODEL by joining every committed mirror (+ optional live clj web-fetch when :live?). kaname.autorun = the heartbeat (cycle = log length; no wall clock / no randomness).",
    "kotobaPersistence": "methods/kotoba.cljc (ADR-2605312345) — persists the leverage readout to the canonical kotoba Datom-log as a content-addressed append-only commit-DAG (shared kotoba.datom binding, 20-actors/kotodama/src): EAVT [:db/add e a v], CID-chained, idempotent-by-content (no append when unchanged), verify-chain tamper-evident, resume-safe, no-server-key, data/persisted/ gitignored. Verified live: beat#0 → 要=OpenAI persisted; beat#1 :no-change; verify-chain {:ok true}.",
    "kotobaBridge": "methods/kotoba_bridge.cljc (founder-approved 2026-06-17, ibuki-R3 pattern) — pushes each local commit-DAG tx to the LIVE kotoba engine via com.etzhayyim.apps.kotoba.datomic.transact. Host allowlist (loopback + EVO-X2 LAN only, ADR-2605215000); graph-cid = KotobaCid::from_bytes parity; :kaname.tx/* provenance; durable :bridge/* cursor (keyed by local CID) = exactly-once; expected_parent optimistic concurrency; DRY-RUN default, live = KANAME_KOTOBA_LIVE=1. VERIFIED LIVE vs running :8077 (2026-06-17): with KANAME_KOTOBA_OPERATOR_DID = the node operator DID (did:key:z6MkiTBz1ymuepAQ4HEHYSF1H8quG5GLVVQR3djdX3mDooWp, loopback node-persists-on-behalf, ibuki-identical) + KANAME_KOTOBA_LIVE=1, committed the readout to the REAL Datom graph: graph bafyreibtzz…, remote tx bafyreiccor…, commit head bafyreigfnz…, 73 datoms confirmed; re-push = no-op (exactly-once proven). The bridge reads KANAME_KOTOBA_OPERATOR_DID from env (fallback). NOTE: the loopback bearer uses the NODE operator DID (the node persists on the actor's behalf); kaname's OWN self-certifying did:key (selfCertifyingDid) is its identity + the member-delegation path.",
    "fleetRegistration": "KanameHeartbeatCell in 50-infra/cluster/murakumo/cell-runner/cells.edn (module kaname.cell, entry fire, node naphtali, cron 53 * * * *, healthz 13083) — the maturity track of ADR-2605192415. kaname.cell/fire runs ONE local heartbeat; live web-fetch + live-engine bridge stay operator-gated.",
    "heartbeatBridge": "kaname.autorun beat takes :bridge? (CLI --bridge): after the local persist it pushes the commit-DAG to the LIVE engine, FAIL-OPEN (engine down / operator DID absent → :bridge {:error …}, the beat still completes locally, never crashes). Verified live: beat#0 appended + bridge pushed=1 datoms=74, beat#1 :no-change + bridge pushed=0 (idempotent on both legs; kotoba/persist! compares against the last LEVERAGE tx, skipping interleaved :bridge/* checkpoints — regression-tested). The cron cell stays local-only; --bridge is the operator-run leg."
  },
  "deployment": "DEPLOYED 実運用 2026-06-17 — per-user macOS LaunchAgent com.etzhayyim.kaname.heartbeat (must run local: depends on LOCAL kotoba :8077 + committed mirror outputs + bb). Hourly at :53, runs deploy/run-heartbeat.sh = autorun --bridge (世界認識 → 要 → persist → push to the LIVE engine); operator DID read dynamically from the running node env (KOTOBA_AGENT_DID, loopback path), bridge fail-opens if the node is down. Verified on install: kickstart beat#0 appended + bridge live pushed=1 datoms=74 (real Datom graph); 2nd kickstart :no-change + pushed=0; agent last-exit 0. Artifacts: 20-actors/kaname/deploy/ (install.clj (bb) install|uninstall|status + plist template + runner + README); generated plist + ~/Library/Logs/kaname-heartbeat.log are machine-local (not committed). Eventual fleet home = KanameHeartbeatCell on node naphtali via cell-runner. Worktree caveat: re-run bb install.clj from the merged checkout after kaname lands on main.",
